=== Displaying code=== <!--T:9-->
</translate>
{{main|Extension:SyntaxHighlight}}
<translate><!--T:10--> If the syntax highlighting extension is available, you can show [[w:source code|source code]] similarly to the HTML <tvar name=1>{{tag|pre|open}}</tvar> tag, but with advanced text editor-like [[w:syntax highlighting|syntax highlighting]].</translate>
<translate><!--T:11--> See the list of supported languages:</translate>
http://pygments.org/languages/
<translate><!--T:12--> Here's an example for displaying [[w:C Sharp (programming language)|C#]] code:</translate>

{{#tag:syntaxhighlight|<syntax<nowiki></nowiki>highlight lang="csharp">
// <translate nowrap><!--T:13--> Hello World in Microsoft C# ("C-Sharp").</translate>

using System;

class HelloWorld
{
    public static int Main(String[] args)
    {
        Console.WriteLine("<translate nowrap><!--T:14--> Hello, World!</translate>");
        return 0;
    }
}
</syntaxhighlight>|lang=wikitext}}

<translate><!--T:65--> Renders as:</translate>

